messages.message:
<!channel> as we become larger, code reviews are going to be become more and more important.  While GitHub has facility to do code reviews, there are other tools out there that have better functionality with regards to reviews and sit on top of GitHub

I’m going to invest some time setting up reviewable.io (http://reviewable.io) (the tool that I am most familiar with).  Let me know if you have any concerns
trying to stay away from completely free open-source tools :slightly_smiling_face: they are usually hard to maintain (Jenkins :smile: )
They have a hosted version too iirc
I’ll look into it as well
I don’t think Phabricator is in the same bucket as Jenkins in terms of too-many-flags.
Just saying we should definitely look into it before committing to one or the other
